\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 Fast forward to another important development in finance to 17th century Netherlands. The Dutch, driven by both necessity and opportunity, found themselves confronting a problem that the simple currency system could no longer solve. A single merchant, no matter how wealthy, could not afford to outfit a ship, hire a crew, and stock it with goods for a two-year journey to the Indies with no guarantee the vessel would ever return. The scale of capital required for these ventures had grown beyond what any individual could reasonably provide, yet the potential rewards were too great to ignore.\
